rComments: She was pretty mediocre, but her way of explaining concepts in simple terms is good. Definitely watch the lectures, but it's the sort of class where even if you study a day before the midterm you'll be fine. No textbook which I liked, but the essay for the final was graded tough by the TAs. Overall, a low effort course.

Dr. Apostolova is a decent prof. Her lectures are quite boring, but that might just be because her areas of interest are boring to me. Very clear on what will be on the exams. If you study you will get a good mark. If you're interested in analytic philosophy, she's a good pick.
Great prof and her exams are extremely easy.

Iva is a great prof! Her midterms and final are extremely fair. It's not an opinion class; you have to memorize the arguments of various bioethicists. Don't bother buying the textbook. Just show up to class, memorize her notes and you'll be golden. The questions she asks on the midterms are basically verbal diarrhea of what she teaches in class.
u just have to memorize all slides like ur name in order to get A+

I have no idea why so many people are bashing her. She's extremely fair. If you go to class and type her notes down, then memorize her notes for the midterms and exam, you'll do well. This class is not an opinion class, it's pure memorization. Don't buy the course pack, it's a waste of money. Stick to the notes she gives you and master those.
Awesome Lady
Very clear expectations and to the point. If you go to class and study your notes you will do well.

I would never take a class with her again. She literally summarizes the textbook in her slides. Her lectures are literally an hour and a half of just her reading slides in a dark room. Doesn't post slides online, so you have to go to class. Tests are hard. TA's are rather harsh markers.

Very clear expectations. Easiest course i had all semester. All you have to do is show up for class and write down the notes, because she doesn't post them online. Her tests were very simple and based on examples we did in class. For the final she uploaded a document with what to expect and the final has the exact same questions.

I found PHI1101 quite boring, her lectures were long but she is very knowledgeable about the subject. You must attend lectures to pass because she does not post slideshows (lengthy slides) on BlackBoard. She provides many examples to fully explain the material and encourages you to read to textbook. Exams are straightforward, but you must study.
Doesn't post lectures online which sucks. Test were pretty tough. Must read textbook and attend all lectures to comprehend course material. Overall it's a decent course.

The lectures are very long and boring as she just directly reads from her slides. She does not post to blackboard therefore, attending class is mandatory to pass. However, she does give a ton of examples and clearly explains them.
Doesn't post slides so you must go to class in order to pass. Is very clear on what will be on tests and provides lots of examples, just go to class and take everything down as notes.

The prof herself was useless as she summarized the text and read off her ppt slides. You need to memorize every word on the slides and every detail in the text to do well. Very boring class as swell. Avoid at all cost.

I took Logic, Epistemology, Philosophical Anthropology, and Applied Ethics with Dr. Apostolova. She is a fantastic teacher, easy to understand, genuinely cares for the welfare of her students, and her expectations are always clear. She is tough but fair with marking. Go to her office hours for a chat!!

Very interesting class and a great prof. Her accent is very soothing to listen to and she explains everything very well. The final was a bit heavy in terms of readings to know in detail but the midterms were more than fair. Read the course pack.

Hot Russian accent made the class pretty intriguing. She just runs through slides and there isn't much class debating for a bioethics class. She is a fairly difficult marker but she's reasonable. i recommend the class because her personality makes it worth while!

Above all else, this professor is incredibly cool and keeps class engaging by making her course relatable and understandable. She teaches the course in an interdisciplinary style, drawing on various other fields, in order to delve into the topics she covers in an holistic and comprehensive manner. Furthermore, its incredibly easy to do well.

She uses her own text package instead of the whole textbook which is super useful. She is passionate and cares about what she is teaching. She is not biased and argues every point if view which is helpful. Very chill teacher and her midterms are pretty easy.

Professor Apostolova's class is both interesting and engaging, but you have to be self-motivated to attend lectures and pay attention (of course). That's the only reason I can see people not liking her, because you need to motivate yourself to study. Otherwise, it was an engaging class!
Do not take bioethics with her. The way she marks is ridiculous for you to even get a B. It is suppose to be an easy course and you end up studying for hours and barely passing the class.

People are crazy. Her class was very clear. PHIL 1101 is a joke. She explains everything in class and the exams are primarily composed of example questions from the lectures. She wrote the textbook and it's like a conversation with the reader. It was informally written making it an easy read. Attend class, read the book, skim your notes = A+
The worst Philosophy prof in the whole university of ottawa! I really do not recommend her. If your registered in her class best thing to do is to switch sections or drop the course

This class was extremely hard.  Her exams/midterms were really tough. The marking scheme was very specific.  The classes were interesting, but when it came to the midterms/exams, they were very difficult to get a good grade. I hated the content!!!! I do not recommend this class.... it is extremely boring, and very hard.
She was a fairly good professor. Classes were interesting and exams were fair. The textbook is her own and I relied on it heavily - it could replace her lecture easily.

Great prof ! Easy to understand and follows the text perfectly. She does not post lecture notes or slides however i rarely went to class and ended with 80 on the final as long as you study the readings you will do good ! We also less you what to study for the final exam. Very straight forward and to the point.

Great professor! Uses multiple examples to help students understand the concepts. Before tests she dedicated some class time for review! She made learning interesting! Easy to approach to  ask questions!

Clear and to the point. She really knows what she's talking about and make critical thinking relatively easy to understand. As long as you go to class you will do fairly well as most of the questions on the midterms are directly from the exercises during the lecture.
Straight to the point, quick exams.

Didn't like her at first, but she's proven to be very flexible (let me write a mid-term during her office hours since I couldn't make one of them) and very clear in the lectures. Plus, there's no assignments. Just a few easy tests and then we're done!

Iva Apostolova is an amazing professor. She is very clear and easy to understand. Her examples are helpful and her lectures are always fun. The material can be confusing at times, but she makes it very understandable. As long as you attend her lectures and listen you will do fine. She is by far one of my favourite professors.
good

Best Prof at uOttawa!  Her lectures are interesting and her accent makes her very easy to listen to.  The class is well structured and she gives you hints on what is on her midterms.  You are able to get an A+ with only studying the night before a midterm. She also gives a take home final exam.

She got harder this semester goddamn hope u don't get her, both the midterms and the final are full of questions which are very philosophical and its impossible to do well in, she also removed her MCQ and fill in the blank...
Pretty laid back course. Very knowledgeable professor. Discussions are interesting. Fair evaluations. Everything was good! 5/5

Easiest course taken in my short university career thus far. Provides notes that you essentially memorize to answer questions on midterms and the final is a take home exam. Professor has almost no accent and allows for discussion of interesting topics pertaining to the course.

This course was very laid back. I studied a day or 2 before each midterm/final and got an A-. If you have time to read the course pack do it as it will serve you well. Make sure to go to class b/c she doesn't post her notes online. Very clear teacher with almost no accent would definitely recommend.

Basically, if you attend the lectures there isn't really a need to read the text book. she teaches very effectively and uses examples to explain everything which i found really helpful. she's really nice, and the midterms are fairly easy, however the exam was a little more difficult. over all, i came away thinking i'd learned something

Very straightforward; just read the coursepack and her notes and you'll do fine. Exams are very straightforward and she gives lots of hints (i.e. tells you the questions beforehand). The course material is super interesting, too. Overall, a great experience.
one of the easiest courses in the philosophy department and her exams are straightforward too.just read the coursepack and youll do fine

Scientific thought and social values: don't take this class if you're a philosophy student. It is meant for the engineering kids and is really boring for someone who studies philosophy. Really easy class though, exams are a joke! A+

Best class I have ever taken. Period. And I'm in the Sciences (Medicine now). I love arguing with her, and she doesn't mind it either. It's the only class where you don't get punished for disagreeing with the teaching of the day. A nice break from learning about enzymatic pathways and****.

She is a very, very sweet woman. She gets right to the lectures and because i haven't even opened the txt, attending lectures are immensely helpful. She has poor grammar at times, but over all a nice and fun lady :)

Great professor. If you can write as fast as she speaks, and make a genuine effort to participate in class, it will be a breeze. Tests have a good level of feedback. The projects and final exam are very interesting. Changed the way I thought about the Arts and prepared me for my medical interview.

Seemed to contradict herself a lot, examples are redundant. Was hard to understand at times. It probably doesn't help that the content is super dull. Seldom went to class (the book is enough to get me by) and still did well

I don't know why others say they cannot understand her because of her accent - she speaks perfect English.  I thought her approach was accurate and fair.  If you attend the class, are awake, read ahead and participate this is the easiest A you will ever get at university.  Good Luck!

Doesn't use the university website.  Does not provide any notes.  Hands back tests late.  Disorganized.  Class syallabus was out of date.  Used an old (unavailable) text in class and made page references to it rather than the text the rest of the class had.  Doesn't really seem interested in teaching.

Very interesting course, greatly enjoyed it. Prof effectively teaches material, sounding neither blandly neutral nor defensive, which is difficult considering the material (abortion, etc). Slides are full of text, and if you don't have a laptop, get them emailed to you, because they aren't online. Overall, enjoyed course.

A good prof. She used powerpoints this year, but still doesn't post notes online, which sucks, considering that her notes are freakishly long, and no one ever has time to write them down. An easy marker. I only went to about 30% of the classes and still got an A. Sometimes hard to understand because of her accent. A bird course I recommend!
Hard marker
Nice Prof., however, I would have enjoyed a little more in-class peer arguments/discussions.
Very helpful
I jas sum Apostolova: http://www.wunrn.com/organizations/human_rights_ngo/hansm.htm

She uses a projector but does not pre-type notes, so you sit and listen to her sounding out words as she types them slowly. I hated the structure of this class, and personally, I found her accent took away from her teaching as it was hard to understand.
Very good prof. Easy marker, easy to understand, addresses questions very clearly.
SOOOO easy! never paid attention in her classes, just read the book and i got a A! she just reads off of her power point presentations and the class gets kind of boring, but it's an easy A
Lovely teacher, did the best she could to make this boring class tolerable.

Nice Prof/very helpful/very knowledgeable.  Class:really boring. Maybe it was content or way of teaching it, but this class made me hesistate to take another philosophy. Didn't add more or explain the philosophers arguments. Liked the interactiveness of typing notes on the overhead during class. Isn't clear on what she wants on tests and exams :S
She types her notes on the overhead while sounding out the words. Her accent makes the class unbearable. But you can skip 90% of the time and still get good marks if you do the reading.

This class is a joke!  It is soo very easy.  I rarely go to lectures, and still managed a 95% on the midterm.  Read the text and you will do fine.  She gets confused a lot and is sometimes hard to undertstand due to her accent.  Also, for a fun time, ask a lot of pointless questions and you will get her off on a tangent for the rest of the time.
I have looked at Philosophy different since taking her class in Fall 2005. She knops what she's doing.

Good ol times sleeping in the class but it's a good to catch up on sleep for other stuff that matters.  This course is ridiculously easy people just go to sit in horrid chairs with no room, conforming with the rest of class.

Classes are extremely boring, but term tests are super easy. If you don't understand what she teacher in her lecture (and don't worry no one ever does) just read the book for clarity. She gets confused alot, so be careful.
REALLLY easy. everything's in the book. But class can get really boring becuse she seems to get confused or lost a lot. She also just repeats exactly what's in the readings

Well, the problem is that there is a small lack of clarity and information. She seems to oversimplify in a pretty bad way that only wets your appetite, but doesn't quite explain why. Philosophy is a difficult matter to teach, but there is definately room for improvement here. She is systematic. Good
I enjoyed her class. Womens studies is an interest of mine as well as philosophy. all in all i think she did a good job on one of her first times as a professor
i enjoyed her class a lot. she always tries to give both sides of the story. you understand that there're no easy answers even in feminism.

1) The lectures make no sense 2) She answers every question with "you're right" 3) The readings make no sense 4) She presents one argument like it's the only argument. Not that she's not nice, but this is just not a way to teach... I always leave her class more confused than when I got there.
